00:00:03.020 --> 00:00:07.080
pork leg 400g, 1/2 onion, green onions 35g

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:09.900
Let's cook "Cha Seung Won Stir-Fried Spicy Pork"

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:28.040
Marinate pork leg in soy sauce 15ml,
crushed garlic 15ml, pepper

00:00:29.420 --> 00:00:55.380
Stir until mixed well

00:00:58.580 --> 00:01:09.260
Cut 1/4 onion into thin slices

00:01:10.980 --> 00:01:16.100
Cut green onion into small pieces

00:01:18.280 --> 00:01:24.140
Grate 1/4 onion

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:36.480
Make sauce with soy sauce 1.5 tbsp, red pepper powder 5 tbsp, sugar 3 tbsp, crushed garlic 1 tbsp, refined rice wine 1 tbsp, sesame oil 1 tbsp, grated 1/4 onion

00:01:42.240 --> 00:01:48.480
Stir sauce ingredients until mixed well

00:01:53.980 --> 00:02:03.060
Place marinated pork leg in a pre-heated pan and stir-fry

00:02:06.140 --> 00:02:17.020
Stir-fry until half done and add the sauce

00:02:17.380 --> 00:02:24.460
Stir until mixed well

00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:30.620
Be careful not to let the suace burn

00:02:32.100 --> 00:02:34.740
Add the cut green onion and oinion

00:02:35.360 --> 00:02:41.820
Stir until mixed well

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:52.360
Sprinkle some sesame and stir until mixed well

00:02:56.960 --> 00:02:59.520
Stir-Fried Spicy Pork Done!

